reviews.text: Really nice surprise to eat at this down-to-earth little Italian place in Wong Chuk Hang. The service was very friendly and helpful, and our food was delicious. Prices are decent!

Our requests for alterations to food due to our allergies were ignored. Puntine pasta soup had only half a dozen pieces of pasta in it. Risotto was dry. Ravioli was more cream sauce than ravioli. At least the pizza is good. If you like Italian food, eat it elsewhere.
Excellent carbonara. But disappointed with the Ceasar salad.
decent food and awesome service. probably only place around with more veggie options
